article.headline: Jacksonville St. 80, SE Missouri State 67
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- B.J. Spencer scored 21 points and Walker Russell added 15 to lead Jacksonville State over Southeast Missouri State 80-67 on Saturday night. Jacksonville State (15-12, 12-8 Ohio Valley) led 19-9 after a 3-pointer by Spencer. However, Southeast Missouri (7-20, 4-16) got within 20-15 after a lay-up by Ketshner Guerrier with 9:19 left in the half. The Gamecocks then went on a 15-3 run and went on to lead 45-23 at halftime. After trailing by as many as 28 points in the second half, the Redhawks got within 71-62 with 4:25 left after a 3-pointer by Paul Paradoski. That was as close as Southeast Missouri could get. Courtney Bradley and Dorien Brown each scored 13 points for Jacksonville State. Roy Booker scored 18 points for Southeast Missouri and Terrick Willoughby had 16.
